                </FooterDetails>
                <Header>Freedom of Information Act (FOIA)</Header>
                <Paragraph>To any person, the FOIA gives a statutory right for obtaining access to Government information that the records of executive branch agencies contain. This right to access is limited, however, when the desired information is shielded from disclosure by any of nine exemptions contained within the statute or three special law enforcement record exclusions.</Paragraph>
